This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with embeddings, which are a fundamental component of many natural language processing models. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of understanding and visualizing embeddings, which is a common topic in the field of NLP. 

The paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as embeddings are widely used in modern machine learning models. 

Furthermore, the paper's methodology of using algebraic formulae to project embeddings into a lower dimensional, semantically meaningful subspace could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing a methodology for analyzing and understanding complex data. 

The paper's use of visualizations could also make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as visualizations are commonly used in this field to understand and analyze image data. 

Finally, the paper's focus on analyzing and comparing multiple sets of embeddings could make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as this is a common task in the field of neural networks.
